love to know!

00:19:58.710 --> 00:20:04.170
What goes on in your personal behind the scene
work when you prepare for each episode?!

00:20:04.170 --> 00:20:12.090
Raj:- Okay, this is what I have found happening
to me, because nowadays I have at least a

00:20:12.090 --> 00:20:17.750
couple of days gap between one Quotidian and
another.

00:20:17.750 --> 00:20:21.110
It takes a while for me to get the next topic.

00:20:21.110 --> 00:20:26.700
The moment I get the next topic, I write it
in a todo-list of sorts.

00:20:26.700 --> 00:20:29.429
And, I have noticed this happening to me.

00:20:29.429 --> 00:20:33.590
Probably that’s what happens to most writers
and creators.

00:20:33.590 --> 00:20:39.270
From that moment on, the moment I nail that
as the topic, anything that happens in my

00:20:39.270 --> 00:20:43.630
life, it could be a movie I am watching on
Netflix, it might be a conversation I am having

00:20:43.630 --> 00:20:51.260
with a colleague, it could be a joke I read
somewhere, I seem to want to do a dotted line

00:20:51.260 --> 00:20:53.660
connection with my theme.

00:20:53.660 --> 00:20:54.660
Okay..

00:20:54.660 --> 00:21:01.179
I have a grab-bag of sorts, I keep throwing
stuff into it once I have a label on the bag.

00:21:01.179 --> 00:21:08.900
And then, I typically work the previous night
on the deck, and so, when I put the deck together,

00:21:08.900 --> 00:21:15.310
the presentation for the video, I look at
the grab-bag, I take them out one by one,

00:21:15.310 --> 00:21:19.150
I look for visuals, look for text, and…
that’s how.

00:21:19.150 --> 00:21:27.610
So, if Quotidians are going theme after theme,
week after week, my mindset is also following

00:21:27.610 --> 00:21:28.610
those things.

00:21:28.610 --> 00:21:30.470
That’s something I have learned about myself!

00:21:30.470 --> 00:21:32.660
Hamsa:- So, aspiring Youtube Creators?!

00:21:32.660 --> 00:21:35.720
